12 subsection in the manner authorized by subsection (e) of this section. If an investment was
13 authorized by this subsection at the time the investment was made or contractually committed to
14 be made, then that investment shall continue continues to be authorized by this subsection, and
15 none of the percentage or other limitation on investments set forth in this subsection shall be
16 construed to require the State Treasurer to subsequently dispose of the investment or fail to honor
17 any contractual commitments as a result of changes in market values, ratings, or other investment
18 qualifications. For purposes of computing market values on which percentage limitations on
19 investments in this subsection are based, all investments shall be valued as of the last date of the
20 most recent fiscal quarter. Notwithstanding anything in this section to the contrary, the State
21 Treasurer shall categorize investment management arrangements according to the primary
22 investment type or primary strategy utilized under the arrangement authorized under subsection
23 (e) of this section. No investment management arrangement may be categorized in more than one
24 of the subdivisions of this section. The State Treasurer shall select from among the following
25 investments subject to the following limitations and requirements:
26 …
27 (13) Digital assets in accordance with G.S. 147-69.2E.
28 …
29 (e) Investments made pursuant to this section may be made as internally managed
30 investments by the State Treasurer Treasurer, or may be made through third-party investment
31 management arrangements, under the following conditions:
32 (1) Internally managed portfolios shall be subject to industry standard portfolio
33 guidelines developed with periodic consultation by the Investment Advisory
34 Committee.
35 (2) In assessing whether to invest directly or to utilize indirect third-party
36 investment management arrangements, the State Treasurer shall consider all
37 material factors he or she considers relevant to the decision consistent with
38 the Treasurer's fiduciary duties under G.S. 147-69.7, including financial,
39 operational, and investment expertise and resources, alignment of interests
40 and investor protections, transparency and repeatability of investment process,
41 risk controls, and cost-effectiveness.
42 (3) For any third-party investment management arrangements, the investment
43 manager must shall have total assets under management of at least one
44 hundred million dollars ($100,000,000) at the inception of the investment
45 management arrangement with the State Treasurer.
46 (4) Third-party investment management arrangements may be with persons and
47 legal entities located within inside or outside the United States, including
48 through any of the following:
49 a. Contractual arrangements in which the investment manager has
50 delegated discretion and authority to invest assets.
